description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen working with the memory service in the Borough of Caerphilly&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will work under the direction of Occupational Therapy as part of an Older Adult mental health service. The role supports the Occupational therapy assessment and treatment of older people with dementia and other mental health problems. Occupational therapists work with people to develop strategies that enable them to engage in the activities that they need and want to do. The ABUHB Older Adult Mental Health Occupational Therapy service, prides itself in delivering quality, person centred care with a focus on evidence based occupational therapy practice. The role is highly valued as part of the wider Older team. Post holders will be supported to access suitable development and training included the relevant AGORED Occupational Therapy support worker qualification.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidates for these posts need to be able to easily form relationships with people - communicate with people who are unable to communicate verbally - think creatively &amp; flexibly to meet the needs of the service - demonstrate empathy, compassion and values of person-centred care and a passion for working with people who live with dementia.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working pattern will be 9am- 5pm. The ability to travel within the borough is an essential requirement of the role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 15th November 2020.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Sophie Parker&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Team Lead Occupational Therapist&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: sophie.parker@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 01443 802403&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please contact Sophie Parker to discuss the role further before application&lt;/p&gt;
